place.name: CLIDDESDEN
place.gazetteerText: CLIDDESDEN, a parish in Basingstoke district, Hants; near the Southwestern railway, 1¾ mile S of Basingstoke. Post town, Basingstoke. Acres, 2, 150. Real property, £2, 431. Pop., 320. Houses, 61. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory, united with the rectory of Farleigh, in the diocese of Winchester. Value, £685.* Patron, the Earl of Portsmouth. The church is old but good. Charities, £15. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
